1
00:00:00,792 --> 00:00:05,338
<i>We need to get the survivors out alive.</i>
<i>We have to get them off this island.</i>

2
00:00:05,922 --> 00:00:08,216
[EMIL] <i>Lucas just gave me a report.</i>
<i>Stay on alert.</i>

3
00:00:08,299 --> 00:00:12,178
<i>I'm sure police officers</i>
<i>are already on the island.</i>

4
00:00:12,262 --> 00:00:14,764
<i>We can't rely on Captain Jacinto now.</i>

5
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:17,308
<i>- What happened?</i>
<i>- He's in detention.</i>

6
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,685
<i>So we've lost our protection?</i>

7
00:00:18,768 --> 00:00:21,354
[EMIL] <i>We still have the hostages.</i>

8
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:22,731
<i>They'll act as our protection.</i>

9
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>Dado. Get one of the hostages</i>
<i>from the banquet hall.</i>

10
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:26,985
[IAN] <i>What for?</i>

11
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:30,613
[EMIL]<i> It's getting too boring for us</i>
<i>and the guests here at the resort.</i>

12
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:32,949
<i>We need to entertain them.</i>

13
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,118
[MAGNUS] <i>I should be out there, not Liam.</i>

14
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:38,413
[WENDY] <i>I know how hard it is for a parent</i>

15
00:00:38,496 --> 00:00:41,458
<i>not to know what's happening</i>
<i>to their child.</i>

16
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,542
<i>I'm sorry, Wendy.</i>

17
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:44,878
<i>You didn't get the chance</i>

18
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:47,005
<i>to be with your son</i>
<i>while he was growing up.</i>

19
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,550
<i>It's all because of Greta.</i>

20
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:51,718
<i>I admire you.</i>

21
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,471
<i>The sacrifices you made for Olsen.</i>

22
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:57,724
<i>I regret how things turned out</i>
<i>between me and my son.</i>

23
00:00:57,807 --> 00:01:00,727
<i>It took a hostage situation happening</i>

24
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:05,190
<i>for me to see how lucky I am</i>
<i>to have a son like him.</i>

25
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:08,401
[PANTING]

26
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:14,532
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

27
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:18,203
[PANTING]

28
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:20,330
- Luna.
- What?

29
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:21,998
Have some water.

30
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:23,625
[PANTS]

31
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:29,130
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:30,298
Here, drink some.

33
00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:33,510
I'm okay. Drink some more.

34
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:37,222
[LUNA] Here.

35
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:41,726
[GULPING]

36
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:47,565
[PANTS, EXHALES]

37
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:54,572
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

38
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:14,342
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC SWELLS]

39
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:16,761
[MAN] Watch your step.

40
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:23,017
- Hey, man. What's the status?
- Cariaso.

41
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:25,520
Cariaso, the shoreline's heavily guarded.

42
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:27,021
Going in would be too risky.

43
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,607
Where can we get through?

44
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:32,485
The north perimeter might work.
Only three are patrolling there.

45
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:35,405
Okay, let's go.

46
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:38,241
Everyone, stay alert.

47
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:39,909
Yes, sir.

48
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:46,416
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:49,878
[MUSIC FADES]

50
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:58,595
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GOON GRUNTING]

51
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:16,237
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:46,267
Here.

53
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:48,937
- Eat this.
- [PANTS, MUNCHES]

54
00:03:50,104 --> 00:03:52,023
[CRUNCHES] Hm.

55
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:58,404
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:03:58,488 --> 00:03:59,697
Look at this.

57
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,662
Dude, I know her.

58
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:08,498
She was here with her friends.

59
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:11,334
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:14,045
She'll never get to be
with her child again.

61
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:22,303
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:27,809
<i>I didn't want to go to jail, Liam.</i>

63
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:30,603
<i>I didn't want to be separated</i>
<i>from you and your dad.</i>

64
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:33,898
<i>I got scared. I didn't know what to do.</i>

65
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:37,151
<i>That's why I talked to Wendy.</i>

66
00:04:37,235 --> 00:04:39,320
<i>But I told her I'd make it up to her.</i>

67
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,073
[MUSIC FADES]

68
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:45,159
Would you do anything for your family?

69
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,453
Even if it's wrong?

70
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,165
What do you mean?

71
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:54,502
What Mama did to Aunt Wendy…

72
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:56,629
That was so wrong.

73
00:04:57,714 --> 00:04:59,382
But her reason

74
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,011
was so she wouldn't be parted from me.

75
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,764
Was that right?

76
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:08,599
In my opinion, dude,

77
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:11,269
it was wrong.

78
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:14,439
But maybe

79
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:17,525
our perspective will change

80
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:19,861
once we become parents ourselves.

81
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:23,364
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:25,199
Here, it's all yours.

83
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:26,743
Let's just split it.

84
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:37,420
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

85
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,423
- Let's go.
- [SOFTLY] Let's go.

86
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:44,719
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYS, FADES]

87
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:52,518
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:08,034
[GUNSHOTS]

89
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:10,328
- [GUNSHOT]
- [BODY THUDS]

90
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:19,837
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:06:31,015 --> 00:06:32,308
[MUSIC FADES]

92
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:41,692
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:54,747
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC BUILDING]

94
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:02,421
Let's go.

95
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:17,812
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

96
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,456
- Take this.
- Hey, wait!

97
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,250
- Get up!
- Wait! Where are you--Hey!

98
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,918
- Wait!
- Shut up!

99
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:43,504
[SOBBING]

100
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:44,714
Take him.

101
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:54,307
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:03,316
This way.

103
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:10,323
- [OFFICER] Sir, clear!
- [AREZA] Move!

104
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:17,079
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:20,708
- [MUSIC FADES]
- [WOMAN WHIMPERS]

106
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:23,252
- [MACKY] Hey!
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

107
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,795
Are you going to kill us?!

108
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:29,467
Even though we're the ones
who can pay you?

109
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,969
Who said we're killing anyone? Huh?

110
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:36,724
All I said is that if someone acts out,
then they die.

111
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:41,437
That's the problem with you rich people.
You think you're powerful.

112
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:44,649
[DADO] You think you can fight back.

113
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:47,026
Let me tell you this.

114
00:08:47,109 --> 00:08:52,031
Until the money's in our hands,
you should all be afraid.

115
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:56,369
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:08:56,452 --> 00:08:59,580
Let me say it one more time.

117
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:02,124
If any of you try to walk out that door

118
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,377
or touch the explosives…

119
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:06,003
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

120
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:08,756
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:10,091
Boom!

122
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:12,885
[DADO] So if you still want to live,

123
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:15,805
don't move.

124
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,057
Are we clear?

125
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,059
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

126
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:24,897
Click, click, boom.
Click, click. Click, click.

127
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,775
[MUSIC STOPS]

128
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:34,991
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC RESUMES]

129
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:38,578
Move.

130
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:45,084
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:09:56,220 --> 00:10:00,516
- [LAUGHING]
- [DEVICE BEEPING]

132
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,810
- Make sure that's secured.
- [GOON] Yes, sir.

133
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:09,900
- [TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFYING]
- [BEEPING CONTINUES]

134
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:20,953
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:31,005
[MOUTHING SILENTLY]

136
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:34,467
[DEVICE BEEPING]

137
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:41,349
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:42,642
They have men everywhere.

139
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:45,853
Sir, let's go up that hill.

140
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:48,981
It'll be safer there.

141
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:54,904
Move.

142
00:10:56,614 --> 00:11:03,621
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:52,128
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:11:53,671 --> 00:12:00,678
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,149
Sir.

146
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:15,317
Sir, that's the house.

147
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,278
- Binoculars.
- Here, sir.

148
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:29,415
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:33,294
Let's move!

150
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:40,384
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:59,528
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,704
Men, they've planted bombs around here.

153
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:26,305
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:38,984
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

155
00:13:39,068 --> 00:13:40,486
Clear!

156
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:42,404
- Clear!
- Clear!

157
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:45,115
Clear!

158
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:46,283
Clear!

159
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:56,210
Clear!

160
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:01,799
Sir, clear!

161
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:14,853
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:19,608
- [METAL CLANKS]
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

163
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,734
[OLSEN] In here.

164
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,456
There are guards everywhere.

165
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:38,669
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,131
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

167
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:46,886
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:50,431
I'll be here for you, okay?

169
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,350
Ready?

170
00:14:54,518 --> 00:14:55,728
Ready.

171
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:59,732
[EMIL] <i>To all our police friends</i>
<i>who are here on the island today,</i>

172
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:02,234
good day.

173
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:06,530
<i>Don't be shy. Show yourselves.</i>

174
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,825
<i>I know you were sent here</i>

175
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:11,911
<i>by Major Domingo.</i>

176
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:15,581
<i>This is a rather small island,</i>

177
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,584
<i>so wherever you hide,</i>

178
00:15:19,543 --> 00:15:22,838
we can surely find you.

179
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:26,967
<i>I don't really appreciate you coming here.</i>

180
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:33,140
<i>The moment you set foot here,</i>
<i>you risked someone's life.</i>

181
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:36,852
So wherever you are now,

182
00:15:37,853 --> 00:15:40,898
I hope you can watch this.

183
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:43,943
<i>Move!</i>

184
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:50,491
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,499
- Sir, please…
- Won't you shut up?

186
00:15:58,582 --> 00:15:59,416
Sir.

187
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,962
[SOBBING] My husband! That's my husband!

188
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:04,421
- Sir…
- In there!

189
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:08,634
<i>Please have mercy on me!</i>

190
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:10,928
That's Mr. Carbonel!

191
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:13,430
I feel bad for him. My goodness!

192
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,516
<i>I'm willing to pay!</i>

193
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,142
Sir!

194
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:20,604
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:22,731
- [DADO] <i>Move it!</i>
- [MR. CARBONEL] <i>I'll pay--</i>

196
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:24,149
<i>- Please…</i>
<i>- Shut up!</i>

197
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,275
<i>Please don't kill me!</i>

198
00:16:27,152 --> 00:16:30,114
Sir! I'm begging you!

199
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:32,282
- Sir! [GRUNTS]
- Don't touch me!

200
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:35,327
- Sir, please!
- You never listen, huh?

201
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:38,330
- Sir! I'll pay you--
- Shut up. Shut up!

202
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,666
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

203
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:44,753
To our police friends, wherever you are,

204
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,382
<i>wherever you're watching this from…</i>

205
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:52,386
<i>don't you feel bad for Mr. Carbonel?</i>

206
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:54,054
<i>I'm sorry, sir.</i>

207
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:57,725
<i>But this is what happens</i>
<i>when cops meddle with our business.</i>

208
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:00,019
Sir, please don't kill me. Sir!

209
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:02,938
<i>Someone has to pay</i>

210
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:04,565
for your intervention.

211
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:07,609
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:11,363
Well then, let's get this over with.

213
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:15,534
- [MRS. CARBONEL] No!
- [GUNSHOTS]

214
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:19,663
[SCREAMING, SOBBING]

215
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:28,130
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:17:32,217 --> 00:17:34,428
[EMIL] <i>I hope you liked</i>

217
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,013
our little show.

218
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,682
Only here on La Playa Roja.

219
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:40,142
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

220
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:43,395
[EMIL] <i>So, to the cops who are still here,</i>

221
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,147
<i>you'd better leave.</i>

222
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:48,942
<i>As you've seen, we're a ruthless bunch.</i>

223
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,279
<i>No one's a VIP.</i>

224
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:57,993
<i>Mr. Carbonel was willing</i>
<i>to pay us 100 million</i>

225
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:00,412
<i>just to save his and his wife's lives.</i>

226
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:07,002
[MRS. CARBONEL WAILING]

227
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,505
And as you've witnessed,

228
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,382
we don't give special treatment.

229
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:14,343
Even VIPs will get killed

230
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:19,389
if you don't do what we want!

231
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:22,726
[EMIL] <i>So just leave.</i>

232
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:28,107
<i>Let us get the ransom,</i>
<i>and we'll be on our way.</i>

233
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:32,069
<i>We have connections back in Alicante.</i>

234
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:36,949
<i>We'll know whether you've returned or not.</i>

235
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:41,787
In one hour,

236
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:44,039
if you still haven't returned to Alicante,

237
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,960
we'll move on to part two.

238
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:59,346
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

239
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:09,231
- Come on. Let's move.
- All right, sir.

240
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:12,609
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

241
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:15,070
[SOBBING]

242
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:21,702
- [SOBBING] My poor husband…
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:19:32,504 --> 00:19:34,798
What should we do, dude?

244
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:36,592
The guards won't leave.

245
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,306
Follow me.

246
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:51,064
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:59,239
